<qhelp>

<overview>
<p>
The <code>MaxRequestLength</code> attribute sets the limit for the input stream buffering threshold in KB. Attackers can use large files to cause denial of service attacks.
</p>

</overview>
<recommendation>

<p>
The recommended value is 4096 but you should try setting it as small as possible according to business requirements.

</p>

</recommendation>


</qhelp>
